        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 2:13PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 213 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Roswell, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roswell and Bitter Lake Wildlife Refuge.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 380 between Mile Markers 156 and 160.
Highway 285 between Mile Markers 103 and 119.
</description>
        <instruction>Heavy rains from severe thunderstorms can produce sudden and
dangerous flows in arroyos, ditches and over low water crossings. Do
not attempt to drive through areas where water covers the roadway.</instruction>
